// Added DrivingCost function to calculate trip driving costs

// Function to compute the cost of driving given the miles driven, vehicle efficiency, and fuel price
Function DrivingCost(float drivenMiles, float milesPerGallon, float dollarsPerGallon) returns float costMiles
   // Calculate total cost: miles driven divided by miles per gallon gives gallons used,
   // multiplied by dollars per gallon gives the cost
   costMiles = drivenMiles * (1.0 / milesPerGallon) * dollarsPerGallon
   return costMiles

Function Main() returns nothing
   float milesPerGallon
   float dollarsPerGallon

   // Prompt user to enter the fuel efficiency of the vehicle (miles per gallon)
   Put "Enter miles per gallon: " to output
   milesPerGallon = Get next input

   // Prompt user to enter the current price of fuel per gallon
   Put "Enter dollars per gallon: " to output
   dollarsPerGallon = Get next input

   // Calculate and output driving cost for 10 miles, formatted to 2 decimal places
   Put DrivingCost(10.0, milesPerGallon, dollarsPerGallon) to output with 2 decimal places
   Put " " to output  // Print a space to separate outputs

   // Calculate and output driving cost for 50 miles, formatted to 2 decimal places
   Put DrivingCost(50.0, milesPerGallon, dollarsPerGallon) to output with 2 decimal places
   Put " " to output  // Print a space to separate outputs

   // Calculate and output driving cost for 400 miles, formatted to 2 decimal places
   Put DrivingCost(400.0, milesPerGallon, dollarsPerGallon) to output with 2 decimal places
